## 1. Login Flow

### Sequence

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant LoginScreen
    participant AuthService
    participant Interceptor as ApiSecurityInterceptor
    participant Server

    User->>LoginScreen: Enter mobile number
    LoginScreen->>LoginScreen: Validate (10-digit, non-empty)
    LoginScreen->>AuthService: generateOtp(mobile, countryCode, idCountry)
    AuthService->>Interceptor: POST auth/generate-otp
    Note over Interceptor: ✅ Encrypts 'mobile' field (RSA-OAEP-SHA256)
    Interceptor->>Server: Encrypted payload
    Server-->>AuthService: {otpReferenceId, success}
    AuthService-->>LoginScreen: OTP reference ID
    LoginScreen->>User: Navigate to OtpScreen
```

### Files Involved

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| [login_screen.dart](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/features/auth/login/login_screen.dart) | UI — mobile number entry, country code picker |
| [auth_service.dart](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/core/services/auth_service.dart) | API calls — `generateOtp()`, `verifyOtp()`, `register()` |
| [api_interceptor.dart](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/core/security/api_interceptor.dart) | Encryption + auth header injection |
| [otp_screen.dart](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/features/auth/otp/otp_screen.dart) | OTP verification + routing logic |

### OTP Verification Sub-Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant OtpScreen
    participant AuthService
    participant SecureStorage
    participant Navigator

    User->>OtpScreen: Enter 6-digit OTP
    OtpScreen->>AuthService: verifyOtp(mobile, otp, referenceId)
    Note over AuthService: POST auth/verify-otp<br/>Fields encrypted: mobile, otp
    AuthService-->>OtpScreen: Response {userExists, mpinEnabled, tokens...}

    alt New User (userExists == false)
        OtpScreen->>Navigator: → RegistrationScreen (temp_token)
        Note over Navigator: Registration → PinCreationScreen → MPIN Setup → Home
    else Existing User + MPIN Enabled
        AuthService->>SecureStorage: Save access + refresh tokens
        OtpScreen->>Navigator: → MpinScreen (unlock)
    else Existing User + MPIN NOT Enabled
        AuthService->>SecureStorage: Save tokens
        OtpScreen->>Navigator: → MpinScreen (setup)
    else Forgot PIN Flow
        OtpScreen->>Navigator: → MpinScreen (reset_pin, temp_token)
    end
```

### Security Assessment

| Check | Status | Notes |
|-------|--------|-------|
| Mobile number encrypted | ✅ | `mobile` is in `sensitiveFields` |
| OTP encrypted | ✅ | `otp` is in `sensitiveFields` |
| Endpoint in encrypted list | ✅ | `auth/generate-otp`, `auth/verify-otp` |
| Auth header skipped for auth endpoints | ✅ | Interceptor excludes `/auth/` paths |
| Token storage uses flutter_secure_storage | ✅ | Via `SecureStorageService` |
| Rate limiting on OTP | ⚠️ | Client-side 30s cooldown only; server-side not verified |

