## 3. Market Socket Update Flow

### Sequence

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant App
    participant NativeSocketService
    participant WebSocket as ws://13.202.62.253:57200
    participant MarketRates
    participant UI as HomeScreen / InstantSaving

    App->>NativeSocketService: connect()
    NativeSocketService->>WebSocket: WebSocket.connect(url, protocols: [token])
    WebSocket-->>NativeSocketService: Connected

    loop Live Rate Updates
        WebSocket-->>NativeSocketService: Raw string data (pipe-delimited)
        NativeSocketService->>MarketRates: MarketRates.fromRawString(data)
        Note over NativeSocketService: Only emits if isSignificantChange()
        NativeSocketService->>UI: ratesStream → StreamProvider
    end

    alt Connection Lost
        NativeSocketService->>NativeSocketService: _scheduleReconnect() → 5s delay → reconnect
    end
```

### Files Involved

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| [native_socket_service.dart](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/core/network/native_socket_service.dart) | WebSocket client — connect, parse, reconnect |
| [market_provider.dart](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/core/providers/market_provider.dart) | Riverpod providers — `marketRatesStreamProvider`, `socketStatusProvider` |

### Key Design Details

- **Protocol Auth**: Socket uses a hardcoded protocol token: `0b286a8b1100f097e7c8e879dbd4174e468a9e92f888e6e289595efdd4747b89`
- **Commodity Config**: `updateCommodityConfig()` dynamically sets gold/silver IDs from the commodities API response
- **Reconnection**: Automatic 5-second retry on disconnect or error
- **Rate Replay**: `ratesStream` getter yields `_lastRate` immediately before streaming, so new subscribers get the latest value instantly
- **Significant Change Filter**: `isSignificantChange()` prevents unnecessary UI rebuilds for micro-fluctuations

### Security Assessment

| Check | Status | Notes |
|-------|--------|-------|
| Socket does not send sensitive data | ✅ | Read-only stream. No user data sent |
| No sensitive data logged | ✅ | `SecureLogger` used; only logs connection status |
| Reconnect on failure | ✅ | 5-second auto-reconnect |
| Socket URL uses plain `ws://` | ⚠️ | **Not WSS**. Data in transit is unencrypted |
| Protocol token is hardcoded | ⚠️ | Should be fetched dynamically or stored securely |
| Payload validation | ✅ | `fromRawString` has try-catch; unknown formats are ignored |

