## 10. MPIN Flow with Biometric

### Sequence

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant App
    participant MpinScreen
    participant SecureStorage
    participant LocalAuth as local_auth
    participant MpinService
    participant Navigator

    App->>MpinScreen: Navigate with args {type: 'unlock' | 'withdrawal_pin' | 'setup' | 'reset_pin' | 'verify_only'}
    MpinScreen->>SecureStorage: Check isMpinEnabled, isBiometricEnabled
    MpinScreen->>LocalAuth: canCheckBiometrics + isDeviceSupported

    alt type != 'withdrawal_pin' && type != 'verify_only' && biometric enabled
        MpinScreen->>LocalAuth: authenticate(localizedReason: "Verify your identity")
        alt Biometric Success
            MpinScreen->>MpinService: verifyMpin (server-side validation may be skipped)
            MpinScreen->>Navigator: → MainScreen (unlock) or pop(pin)
        else Biometric Cancelled / Failed
            MpinScreen->>User: Fall back to keypad entry
        end
    end

    alt Manual MPIN Entry
        User->>MpinScreen: Enter 4-digit PIN on shuffled keypad
        MpinScreen->>MpinService: verifyMpin(pin)
        Note over MpinService: POST mpin/validate<br/>Encrypted: mpin
        MpinService-->>MpinScreen: success/failure

        alt Success
            MpinScreen->>Navigator: Navigate based on type
        else Failure
            MpinScreen->>MpinScreen: Increment failedAttempts (5 = lock)
        end
    end
```

### MPIN Types & Routing

| `type` Argument | Purpose | Biometric Allowed | After Success |
|----------------|---------|:-----------------:|---------------|
