## 12. Findings & Recommendations

### ❌ Critical Issues

| # | Issue | Location | Risk | Recommendation |
|---|-------|----------|------|----------------|
| **C1** | **HTTP Base URL** | [app_config.dart:4](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/core/config/app_config.dart#L4) | All API traffic is plaintext; RSA encryption only protects individual fields, not the full HTTP payload or headers | **Switch to HTTPS immediately** for production |
| **C2** | **Socket uses `ws://` not `wss://`** | [native_socket_service.dart:9](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/core/network/native_socket_service.dart#L9) | Market rate data can be intercepted/manipulated via MITM | Use `wss://` with TLS |

### ⚠️ Medium Issues

| # | Issue | Location | Risk | Recommendation |
|---|-------|----------|------|----------------|
| **M1** | **Hardcoded socket protocol token** | [native_socket_service.dart:10-12](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/core/network/native_socket_service.dart#L10-L12) | Token leaked in source code; can be extracted from APK | Fetch auth token dynamically from server after login |
| **M2** | **`device_id` is placeholder** | [saving_service.dart:30](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/features/instant_saving/services/saving_service.dart#L30) | Device fingerprinting for fraud detection is non-functional | Use `device_info_plus` package for real device ID |
| **M3** | **Cert pinning placeholders** | [app_config.dart:28-30](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/core/config/app_config.dart#L28-L30) | No certificate pinning → vulnerable to MITM even with HTTPS | Implement real cert fingerprints when moving to HTTPS |
| **M4** | **`id_customer` commented out** in withdrawal APIs | [withdrawal_service.dart:34,45,92,109](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/features/withdrawal/services/withdrawal_service.dart#L34) | Server may not be validating which customer is requesting the withdrawal | Ensure server extracts customer ID from the auth token |
| **M5** | **Biometric auth doesn't re-verify MPIN on server** | [mpin_screen.dart](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/features/mpin/mpin_screen.dart) | On biometric success for unlock, the MPIN isn't sent to server; relies on local biometric only | For unlock scenarios this is acceptable; for any transactional flow, MPIN must be verified server-side |
| **M6** | **`profile/accountdetails`** not in encrypted endpoints | [withdrawal_service.dart:15](file:///d:/Git/SIP/lib/features/withdrawal/services/withdrawal_service.dart#L15) | `mobile` field will still be encrypted (it's in `sensitiveFields`), but endpoint itself isn't flagged | Consider adding to encrypted endpoints if response contains bank details |

### ℹ️ Low / Informational Issues

| # | Issue | Location | Notes |
|---|-------|----------|-------|
| **L1** | OTP rate limiting is client-side only | `otp_screen.dart` | 30-second cooldown; server should enforce its own limits |
| **L2** | `debugPrint` statements remain in MPIN screen | `mpin_screen.dart:77-99` | Should be removed or replaced with `SecureLogger` in release |
